                        <p>The final layer of believability came from the small details: simulating dust particles floating in the air, adding subtle lens flares from the station's lights, and ensuring every reflection on the actors' helmets accurately mirrored the CG environment. These are the elements that sell the shot and immerse the audience completely in the world we've built.</p>
